stackcomp start variants test helper (tty/nested, release/debug, crashdump)
=============================================================================

Purpose
-------
Quick runbook for validating launcher behavior in native and nested sessions,
including environment overrides, release/debug modes, and crash logging paths.

Key paths
---------
Project root: <your_local_repo>/scratch-compositor
Binary:       <your_local_repo>/scratch-compositor/build/stackcomp
Launcher:     <your_local_repo>/scratch-compositor/testing/stackcomp_run
Env file:     <your_local_repo>/scratch-compositor/config/environment
Default cfg:  <your_local_repo>/scratch-compositor/testing/stackcomp.conf

Runtime log location
--------------------
Default runtime state/log base:
  $XDG_STATE_HOME/stackcomp
Fallback when XDG_STATE_HOME is unset:
  ~/.local/state/stackcomp

Note:
The `stackcomp` suffix is the fixed project runtime namespace.
It is independent of launcher install path/name (for example /usr/bin/stackcomp).

Typical files:
  stackcomp.log
  stackcomp-crash.log
  stackcomp-startup.log
  stackcomp-shutdown.log
  stackcomp-nested-startup.log
  stackcomp-nested-shutdown.log
  shutdown_list.nfo

Pre-checks
----------
1) Build once:
   ninja -C build

2) Verify binary exists:
   test -x ./build/stackcomp && echo OK || echo MISSING

3) Optional: verify xwayland-satellite is available:
   command -v xwayland-satellite || echo "xwayland-satellite not in PATH"


A) Launcher config model
------------------------
The launcher resolves settings in this order:
1) Caller environment (one-shot VAR=... ./testing/stackcomp_run)
2) STACKCOMP_ENV_FILE (if set)
3) config/environment (if present)
4) Built-in defaults in testing/stackcomp_run

Note:
config/environment is override-oriented. Values can stay commented out.


B) Debug mode matrix (STACKCOMP_DBG)
------------------------------------
STACKCOMP_DBG=0 (release default):
- --log-level error
- --no-crash-handler

STACKCOMP_DBG=1:
- --log-level info
- crash handler remains off

STACKCOMP_DBG=2:
- --log-level debug
- crash handler on (--crash-log)


C) Native test (TTY / DRM+libinput)
-----------------------------------
Run from a VT/TTY (outside another desktop session):

  cd <your_local_repo>/scratch-compositor
  ./testing/stackcomp_run

Check:
- startup summary contains session mode native-tty
- WLR_BACKENDS is drm,libinput
- run exits cleanly or emits actionable errors


D) Nested test (inside X11 or Wayland session)
----------------------------------------------
Run from terminal inside existing desktop session:

  cd <your_local_repo>/scratch-compositor
  ./testing/stackcomp_run

Check:
- startup summary shows nested-x11 or nested-wayland
- WLR_BACKENDS is x11 or wayland
- nested startup/shutdown logs are used


E) X11 bridge behavior (xwayland-satellite)
-------------------------------------------
Session-aware default when STACKCOMP_X11 is unset:
- nested (x11/wayland): STACKCOMP_X11 defaults to 0
- native (drm,libinput): STACKCOMP_X11 defaults to 1

Force disable:
  STACKCOMP_X11=0 ./testing/stackcomp_run

Force enable:
  STACKCOMP_X11=1 ./testing/stackcomp_run

Force X11 display:
  STACKCOMP_X11_DISPLAY=:12 ./testing/stackcomp_run

Confirm:
  rg -n "xwayland-satellite|DISPLAY=|WAYLAND_DISPLAY=|STACKCOMP_X11" "$XDG_STATE_HOME"/stackcomp/*.log


F) Config override test
-----------------------
Use alternate config without editing launcher:

  STACKCOMP_CFG=/path/to/other.conf ./testing/stackcomp_run

Check startup summary line:
- "Config file path: ... (override from STACKCOMP_CFG)"


G) Log directory override test
------------------------------
Route logs to custom path:

  STACKCOMP_LOG_DIR=/tmp/stackcomp-test ./testing/stackcomp_run

Check:
  ls -1 /tmp/stackcomp-test


H) Direct binary test (bypass launcher)
---------------------------------------
Use when validating compositor flags directly:

  cd <your_local_repo>/scratch-compositor
  ./build/stackcomp \
    -c ./testing/stackcomp.conf \
    --log-level debug \
    --log-file ~/.local/state/stackcomp/stackcomp.log \
    --crash-log ~/.local/state/stackcomp/stackcomp-crash.log


I) Crashdump path test (intentional)
------------------------------------
Use only to validate crash marker output:

  cd <your_local_repo>/scratch-compositor
  ./build/stackcomp \
    -c ./testing/stackcomp.conf \
    --log-level debug \
    --log-file ~/.local/state/stackcomp/stackcomp.log \
    --crash-log ~/.local/state/stackcomp/stackcomp-crash.log \
    --crash-test

Expected:
- process terminates due to deliberate SIGSEGV
- crash marker appears in stackcomp-crash.log
- startup log reports non-zero exit and summary lines


J) Fast triage commands
-----------------------
Set once for convenience:
  LOG_BASE="${XDG_STATE_HOME:-$HOME/.local/state}/stackcomp"

Recent error scan:
  rg -n -i "warn|warning|error|failed|crash|segv|sig" "$LOG_BASE"/*.log

Check startup core lines:
  rg -n "Selected session mode|WLR_BACKENDS|WLR_WL_SOCKET|STACKCOMP_DBG|STACKCOMP_X11|Config file path" "$LOG_BASE"/stackcomp*-startup.log

Check crash markers only:
  rg -n -i "crash|segv|signal|backtrace" "$LOG_BASE"/stackcomp-crash.log


K) Suggested test sequence
--------------------------
1) ninja -C build
2) STACKCOMP_DBG=0 ./testing/stackcomp_run (baseline release mode)
3) STACKCOMP_DBG=1 ./testing/stackcomp_run (release-debug logs)
4) STACKCOMP_DBG=2 ./testing/stackcomp_run (debug + crash handler)
5) STACKCOMP_CFG=/path/to/alt.conf ./testing/stackcomp_run
6) Optional nested run with STACKCOMP_X11=0 and then STACKCOMP_X11=1

